text.tspan: Death rates from ambient particulate air pollution vs. GDP per capita, 2017
Deaths attributed to exposure to outdoor particulate air pollution, measured as the number of premature deaths per
100,000 people versus gross domestic product (GDP) per capita, measured in 2011 international-$. Death rates
are age-standardized, so correct for differences in age structures between populations.
Deaths from ambient particulate air pollution (per 100,000)
Source: IHME, Global Burden of Disease; World Bank
